A tragic shooting at a Nebraska mall left eight dead, including the gunman, Robert A. Hawkins.
The incident, described as random and without provocation, shocked the nation.
Hawkins, who had a troubled past, left a suicide note expressing remorse.
Victims included employees and customers, with others injured.
Witnesses described chaos and fear as gunshots rang out.
The community mourns the senseless loss of life.
President Bush, who was in Omaha at the time, expressed sadness over the tragedy.
The motive behind Hawkins' actions remains unclear, leaving many searching for answers.
